<h1>Floating Buttons</h1>
<p>
	Floating Buttons are buttons that are supposed to go over some element (like an image)
	and provide additional actions for the user.
	Floating Button supports <code>&lt;button&gt;</code> and <code>&lt;a&gt;</code> elements.
	To use it simply add <code class="format-code">.wds-floating-button</code> class.
</p>
<p>
	Multiple Floating Buttons should be placed inside <code class="format-code">.wds-floating-button-group</code>.
	The <code class="format-code">.wds-floating-button-group</code> can be either horizontal or vertical. By
	default the orientation is horizontal and can be switched by using addtional class - <code class="format-code">.wds-is-vertical</code>.
</p>

